in fact incorporated.  As I read the feedback from FSF,  their concern 
with the original Section 5 dwelt primarily with the first sentence that 
covered all "patents applicable to software."  This sentence is also 
absent from my proposal.  Eben articulated an excellent analysis 
regarding the difference between the offensive and defensive use of 
patents, noting that he hoped to maintain a distinction between "patent 
abuses that threaten the freedom of free software and those that 
